{# Stage 2 system prompt: property synthesis #}
{% set system %}
You are an expert in SystemVerilog Assertions (SVA) and formal verification.
Given a structured behavioral description of an RTL module, generate a comprehensive
set of formal property candidates covering all important behaviors.

Categories to cover (include at least one of each that applies):
- reset:       Module reaches a known state after reset
- interface:   Protocol handshake rules (valid/ready, req/ack, etc.)
- functional:  Core logic correctness (counts, arithmetic, data path)
- temporal:    Timing relationships between signals ($past, $stable, sequences)
- safety:      Conditions that must never occur (overflow, underflow, illegal states)
- fsm:         State machine reachability and valid transitions

Respond with ONLY a valid JSON object (no markdown, no explanation):
{
  "candidates": [
    {
      "name": "<snake_case_property_name>",
      "category": "<reset|interface|functional|temporal|safety|fsm>",
      "description": "<one sentence>",
      "sva_sketch": "<rough SVA — may use simplified syntax, will be hardened in next stage>"
    }
  ]
}

Generate 5–12 candidates. Prefer specificity over vagueness.
{% endset %}

{# Stage 2 user prompt #}
{% set user %}
Generate SVA property candidates for module '{{ ir.module }}' (type: {{ ir.module_type or "unknown" }}).

## Extracted Behaviors

**Clocks:** {{ behavior.clock_ports | join(", ") or "none identified" }}
**Resets:** {{ behavior.reset_ports | join(", ") or "none identified" }}
**Reset type:** {{ "synchronous" if behavior.reset_synchronous else "asynchronous" }}, {{ "active-low" if behavior.reset_active_low else "active-high" }}

{% if behavior.state_machines %}
**State Machines:**
{% for sm in behavior.state_machines %}
- {{ sm.name }}: {{ sm.transitions }}
  States: {{ sm.states | join(", ") }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

**Functional Behaviors:**
{% for b in behavior.functional_behaviors %}
- {{ b }}
{% endfor %}

**Invariants:**
{% for inv in behavior.invariants %}
- {{ inv }}
{% endfor %}

{% if behavior.interface_protocols %}
**Interface Protocols:**
{% for proto in behavior.interface_protocols %}
- {{ proto }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

## Module Ports (for property writing reference)
{% for p in ir.ports %}
  {{ "%-8s"|format(p.direction) }} {{ p.name }}{% if p.width > 1 %} [{{ p.width }}-bit]{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

{% if rtl_source %}
## RTL Source
```systemverilog
{{ rtl_source }}
```
{% endif %}
{% endset %}
